1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,960
a:padam apaharta:ram da:ta:ram
sarvasampadam

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:19,000
lo:ka:bhi:ra:mam Shri:ra:mam bhu:yo bhu:yo
nama:myaham

3
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Jai Shri:man Na:ra:yana!

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Dear devotees of Bhagava:n,

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:38,000
when we start a task,

6
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
why are we doing that work?

7
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,000
What is its purpose?

8
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Who all are involved in it?

9
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,960
What should we do?

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:56,000
We begin that task after understanding all
these aspects.

11
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Similarly, if we want to read a book,

12
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,000
why should we read it?

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
What should we know?

14
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,960
What is the benefit of reading it?

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:23,000
If we understand this and feel it is
beneficial,

16
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,000
then we can decide to read another book.

17
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
The 'Bhagavad Gi:tha' too,

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,000
for whom is it intended?

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,000
What should we know?

20
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:45,000
We should understand this before starting
to read the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'.

21
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Generally, everyone says that the
'Bhagavad Gi:tha' is a great book,

22
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
but what is its purpose?

23
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,960
For whom is the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha' meant?

24
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:14,584
It covers business management, personality
development, science, philosophy,

25
00:02:14,624 --> 00:02:16,000
theology.

26
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:22,000
It contains many morals.

27
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,960
We often discuss the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha',

28
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:32,000
but when we open that book,

29
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
what should we learn from it?

30
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,000
What should we understand from it?

31
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
If we have a clear understanding,

32
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
we try to understand it from that
perspective.

33
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:56,000
If we call a Prime Minister and ask him to
clear the roads,

34
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
he can indeed clear the roads.

35
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
He has already arranged for the roads to
be cleaned.

36
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,000
But if the purpose is just to clear the
roads,

37
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,000
he does not need to do it himself,

38
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:16,000
as there is someone else assigned to that
task.

39
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,960
there are some things that only this
person can do,

40
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:28,000
so when it is important for us to learn
from him,

41
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:33,000
we should approach him.

42
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Other than that, when a person says
something,

43
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
whether it is good or bad,

44
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,000
it reveals what kind of ignorance we have.

45
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:51,000
This understanding helps us see

46
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
the nature of our ignorance.

47
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:03,000
When we present a book like the 'Bhagavad
Gi:tha',

48
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,000
what is its purpose?

49
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Is it only to teach science?

50
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
To teach science, we need scientific
books,

51
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,000
and we can follow those happily.

52
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,000
We can learn from them.

53
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,960
Is it necessary to take the 'Bhagavad
Gi:tha' and learn from it?

54
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
It is not necessary.

55
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,000
To learn morals,

56
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
we need books that teach morals,

57
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:38,000
and we can learn from those happily.

58
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Is the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha' meant to teach us
management skills?

59
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,960
There are many management courses,

60
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,000
and if we go there happily,

61
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
they will teach us all the details about
it.

62
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,000
we can learn from them.

63
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Is it meant to teach us dietary rules?

64
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:07,000
There are so many doctors and physicians,

65
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
we can learn from them.

66
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,000
But is the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha' meant to
teach or not?

67
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:19,000
If we know the purpose of the 'Bhagavad
Gi:tha',

68
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:25,000
then wherever we go, whatever we see,

69
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
we should ask, will it take us to that
goal?

70
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Or are we able to reach that goal through
it?

71
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,960
Is it meant to teach or not?

72
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
It is our responsibility to know that

73
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
That is why it is our responsibility to
know it,

74
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:48,000
and understand the main purpose of the
'Bhagavad Gi:tha'.

75
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
In this context,

76
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
it was to teach Arjuna his duty.

77
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,000
He started for that purpose,

78
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,000
mainly for that reason alone.

79
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:07,000
After teaching Arjuna,

80
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
his work was complete.

81
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,000
There was no need for anything else.

82
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,000
We don't need anything more in this era.

83
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:24,000
No, it was left solely for that purpose.

84
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,000
But the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'

85
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
is not a book only for Arjuna

86
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,000
or just for the war.

87
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Then, what is it for?

88
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
It is for the human race.

89
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
When they are born on this earth,

90
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,000
before they die,

91
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:54,000
if they do the work they are supposed to
do,

92
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
they will be able to achieve it.

93
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,000
This must be conveyed.

94
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
How should they perform the work they are
meant to do?

95
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
For the human race,

96
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,000
this is important.

97
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
How should they fulfill their duty?

98
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,000
It is crucial for a human being to
understand

99
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,000
that saying this

100
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:27,000
is the main purpose of Krishna's
incarnation in this world.

101
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,960
Arjuna,

102
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,000
with a specific purpose,

103
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
was part of a plan,

104
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,000
and through him, Krishna fulfilled it.

105
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,000
This is what we should understand.

106
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,000
There are additional aspects to this.

107
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,000
yuktha:ha:ra viha:rasya,

108
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,000
learn how to eat properly.

109
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,000
yuktha svapna:vabo:dha:sya,

110
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,000
early to bed, early to rise.

111
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,000
There are guidelines like these.

112
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:03,000
There are other rules,

113
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
but to explain those rules,

114
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,000
what is their purpose?

115
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
What is the duty of a human being?

116
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
What should he do?

117
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,000
For the common man,

118
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,000
this is the purpose of the 'Bhagavad
Gi:tha'.

119
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
That is why the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'

120
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
is divided into three parts.

121
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,000
The first part consists of six chapters.

122
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
The second part also consists of six
chapters,

123
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,000
and the third part has six chapters as
well.

124
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Altogether, there are eighteen chapters.

125
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,000
The first six chapters

126
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:51,000
aim to reveal the true nature of the soul.

127
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,000
We don't find these teachings elsewhere,

128
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,960
not in management courses,

129
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
not in moral teachings,

130
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,000
not in scientific studies,

131
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,000
nor in any other places.

132
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,000
To understand these concepts,

133
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,000
you must turn to the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'.

134
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,000
To approach the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha',

135
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,000
you need to seek it out,

136
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,000
and you have to understand it.

137
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,960
if you don't know the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha',

138
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,000
there's no need to worry.

139
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,000
You don't have to search for it,

140
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,000
because it will come to you.

141
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,000
The first six chapters

142
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,000
are called 'A:thma Shatkam'.

143
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,000
They provide a detailed description of the
a:thma thatthva.

144
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,000
The second six chapters

145
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,000
are called 'Bhakti Shatkam'.

146
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Bhakti means love,

147
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:55,000
and you must have this love in any
thatthva.

148
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,000
This love is emphasized in the 'Bhagavad
Gi:tha'.

149
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Who is the one in the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'?

150
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,000
What is his nature?

151
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,000
Where does he reside?

152
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,000
What will he do?

153
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,000
What is your relationship with him?

154
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,000
What do you have to do with him?

155
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,000
What do you expect from him?

156
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
How far is that possible?

157
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,000
You have to know all these,

158
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,000
to understand the essence of the 'Bhagavad
Gi:tha'.

159
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:24,000
The six chapters in the middle of the
'Bhagavad Gi:tha'

160
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,000
are called the Bhakti Shatkam.

161
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,000
This is the name of the second Shatkam.

162
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,000
After saying this,

163
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Arjuna had some doubts.

164
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,000
If I say this,

165
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,000
can I solve this?

166
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:43,960
He had the courage,

167
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,000
and after saying this,

168
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,000
the first six chapters,

169
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,000
the second six chapters,

170
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,000
out of the twelve chapters,

171
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,000
he followed a systematic order.

172
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,000
He did a thorough analysis.

173
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:00,000
There are some pauses,

174
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,000
some connecting points,

175
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,000
and if there are any,

176
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,000
he combined all of them.

177
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,000
To convey all of them,

178
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:09,960
the last six chapters,

179
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,000
he called it

180
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Purva Sesham.

181
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,000
Purva Sesham.

182
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,000
he called it

183
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,000
Migulu.

184
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,000
He called it

185
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,000
In this way,

186
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,000
he divided it into three parts.

187
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,000
Chapter 18

188
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,000
is the Grantham.

189
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Arjuna,

190
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:34,960
as a reason,

191
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,000
as a reason,

192
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,000
Sri: Krushna

193
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,000
considered it an important

194
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Grantham,

195
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,000
Adhya:thma Grantham,

196
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,000
the 'Bhagavad Gi:tha'.

197
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,000
In this,

198
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,000
the first four chapters

199
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,000
address

200
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,000
Arjuna's heart.

201
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,000
A

202
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,000
soka

203
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,000
or Visha:da

204
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,000
needed to be opened.

205
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,000
He needed

206
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
vive:chana.

207
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Vive:chana means

208
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,000
the ability to analyze.

209
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,000
The capacity was reduced.

210
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,000
What should be analyzed?

211
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,000
The body.

212
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,000
the a:thma,

213
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,000
to be able to analyze,

214
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,000
to be able to discern,

215
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,000
is very important

216
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,000
to benefit from the sa:dhanas.

217
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,000
God said,

218
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,000
vimoka,

219
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:35,960
abhya:sa,

220
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:36,960
kriya,

221
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,960
anava:sa:da,

222
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:38,960
kalya:na,

223
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,960
anudharsha.

224
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:40,960
In this way,

225
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,000
He told us about seven sa:dhanas.

226
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,960
Among those seven sa:dhanas,

227
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,000
the very first sa:dhana

228
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
He started with is vive:kam.

229
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Vive:kam means intelligence.

230
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,000
No,

231
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,960
vive:kam means

232
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
the ability to separate and see.

233
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:58,960
That is the meaning of

234
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,000
vive:chana.

235
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,000
What should be done in vive:chana?

236
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,000
That is,

237
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:07,960
the body

238
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:08,960
and the a:thma.

239
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,000
These two are different.

240
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,000
We should start from here.

241
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,000
How do we know

242
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,000
how to identify the first sa:dhana?

243
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,960
If the food you eat is good,

244
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,960
everything will be good.

245
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,000
The food you eat should indeed be good.

246
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,960
If your thoughts are good,

247
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,000
first, you should put good food inside.

248
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,000
The 'indhanam' should be good.

249
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,000
'Indhanam' is the food we eat.

250
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,000
So, should we put good food inside?

251
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,000
So, what is considered good food?

252
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,960
Depending on what,

253
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,000
we determine the goodness of the food.

254
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,000
We decide based on whether it is

255
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:43,960
sa:thvikam,

256
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,960
ra:jasam,

257
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,000
or ta:masam.

258
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,000
We should remember these categories.

259
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,960
Whatever is not good,

260
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,000
we should put it aside.

261
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,960
Whatever is necessary,

262
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,000
we should accept it.

263
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:56,960
And the food we eat,

264
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:57,960
the food we eat

265
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,000
affects us.

266
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Whatever thoughts you have,

267
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,960
this body,

268
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:05,960
this a:thma,

269
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:06,960
these two,

270
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,000
if we are able to separate and see,

271
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:09,960
then it is called

272
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,000
vivekam.

273
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Aahaara Suddhi.

274
